flowRoot.flowPara: Howard is an experienced hosting user. He is comfortable with basic system administration and has a VPS with a hosting provider that he uses to run web apps for family and friends, personal projects, and a few production apps that earn him a bit of money through advertising. He isn't very familiar with cloud concepts like PaaS, but has heard a lot of talk about it and wants to try it out for himself.

Ted is a manager for a web company and wants to improve his understanding of the technical side of the industry. He's been educating himself by reading industry publications and going to conferences. He's heard of other PaaS's like Heroku and Google App Engine, but haven't used them. He's familiar with the basic concepts of cloud and why it matters. He heard about OpenShift at a conference he attended and wants to learn more about it by trying out.

Twyla is all about performance. She's developed a number of web apps, and loves to continually tweak her configurations and optimizations in order to get the most out of them. She deeply understands the way components of a software stack interact and is completely comfortable with the command-line, and editing text-based configuration files. She understands that PaaS can potentially save a lot of time, so she's shopping around for one that will save her time on stuff she doesn't care about, but still let her play around with configurations and optimizations.

Neely is an experienced web developer with no interest in system administration. She knows PaaS is a good fit for her, but before she commits to any PaaS, she needs to know she'll be able to run her existing apps on the service and that it will support future projects in the frameworks she prefers.
